<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 30 at 8:16AM CDT  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...AREAS OF FOG THIS MORNING...
Current observations are indicating fog reducing visibilities to
between 1 and 3 miles, with isolated pockets of denser fog
reducing the visibility to around one half-mile. The fog is
expected to lift between 9AM and 10AM CDT this morning.
Use caution during the morning commute, as visibility may change
rapidly in a short amount of time. Use low beam headlights and
leave extra distance between your vehicle and others on the road.</description>
